      • getSelectedDomain

      • getVisibleDomains

        public Collection<WebCmsDomain> getVisibleDomains()
        Returns the domains from which entities are currently selectable (visible domains). Usually this is the current domain, however if the current multi-domain configuration allows no-domain this collection will also contain null.
        Returns:
        collection of domains - possibly including a null value

      • getAccessibleDomains

        public Collection<WebCmsDomain> getAccessibleDomains(com.foreach.across.modules.spring.security.actions.AllowableAction... actions)
        Returns all domains that the current principal can select. Optionally takes one or more AllowableAction parameters that the principal should have for that domain. Note that in case of multiple parameters, it is an OR construct: as soon as the user has any of those actions allowed the domain will be included.

        If no AllowableAction is specified, it will default to AllowableAction.READ.

        If no-domain is allowed, will check if the user has the permissions to manage the WebCmsDomain type itself.

      • visibleDomainsPredicate

        public com.querydsl.core.types.Predicate visibleDomainsPredicate(QWebCmsDomain domain)
        Create a domain binding predicate for a QueryDSL path of a WebCmsDomain property. This will check the multi-domain configuration and create a domain predicate if necessary. This method can return a null value but should be safe to use with QueryDSL expression utils.
        Parameters:
        domain - expression (property linked to the WebCmsDomain)
        Returns:
        predicate or null

        original or appended predicate
